🎨 Full Multi-Modal Support

We're excited to announce that Langfuse Tracing now offers full multi-modal support
[https://langfuse.com/docs/tracing-features/multi-modality], including images, audio files, and attachments! This highly requested
feature allows you to integrate media such as images (PNG, JPG, WEBP), audio files (MPEG, MP3, WAV), and documents (PDF, plain
text) directly into your traces, enhancing your development and monitoring workflow in Langfuse.
Getting started is easy—simply upgrade to the latest version of the Langfuse SDK. Our SDKs now automatically handle base64 encoded
media, extracting and uploading them independently while referencing them in your traces. For more control or different media
types, you can use the new LangfuseMedia class to wrap your media before inclusion or upload directly via API.
🕹️ Get Started: Check out our changelog [https://langfuse.com/changelog/2024-11-20-full-multi-modal-images-audio-attachments] to
learn how this feature works under the hood and to get started.
 


