⏮️ All releases of Launch Week #2

 * 🔻 Day 0: Langfuse Prompt Management [https://langfuse.com/docs/prompts/get-started] now integrates natively with the Vercel AI
   SDK. Version and release prompts in Langfuse, use them via Vercel AI SDK, monitor metrics in Langfuse. (Twitter
   [https://x.com/marcklingen/status/1858145579789943233?sF], Changelog
   [https://langfuse.com/changelog/2024-11-17-vercel-ai-sdk-prompt-mgmt])

 * 🌓 Day 1: Langfuse Datasets [https://langfuse.com/docs/datasets/overview] now offers a powerful comparison view for dataset
   experiment runs. It's perfect for teams iterating on their AI applications with different prompts, models, or parameters who
   want to quickly see the results of a change in a side-by-side with their benchmark version. (Twitter
   [https://x.com/MarcKlingen/status/1858539441813410139], Changelog
   [https://langfuse.com/changelog/2024-11-18-dataset-runs-comparison-view])

 * ⚖️ Day 2: Datasets in Langfuse allow you to create test sets and benchmarks to evaluate the performance of your LLM
   application. Until now, Dataset Experiments required custom evaluations added via SDKs or APIs. Starting today, you can use
   LLM-as-a-Judge Evaluators on the Datasets you maintain in Langfuse. (Twitter
   [https://x.com/MarcKlingen/status/1858987480411730280], Changelog
   [https://langfuse.com/changelog/2024-11-19-llm-as-a-judge-for-datasets])

